Hello,

This is probably because SciViews-K cannot find R. You have to indicate 
which R version you want to use with Komodo by entering this information 
in the Windows registry. This is simply done by running RSetReg.exe from 
the /bin subdirectory of the R version you want to use (by default 
install dirs, this will be something like 'c:/Program 
Files/R/R-x.y.z/bin/RSetReg.exe'). I think you don't have to restart 
Komodo or Windows, but just in case it still does not work, restart 
everything and try again.

Note that you can use this trick to switch from R 2.8.1 to 2.9.1 and 
vice versa.

Note also that a new version of SciViews-K with lot more features and 
compatible with the latest Komodo Edit 5.2 will be released very soon 
(that is, when I will have done the Komodo's code intelligence for R, 
which appears rather tricky)!

Best,

Philippe Grosjean

